        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 26 at 8:25PM CDT until May 26 at 9:30PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Collingsworth County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Donley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 930 PM CDT.

* At 825 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles southwest
of Hedley, or 10 miles northwest of Memphis, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southwestern Collingsworth and southeastern Donley Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
